	(text "Pull-Up During Configuration (bar)\nActive-Low PUDC_B input enables internal pull-up resistors\non the SelectIO pins after power-up and during configuration.\n• When PUDC_B is Low, internal pull-up resistors are\n   enabled on each SelectIO pin.\n• When PUDC_B is High, internal pull-up resistors are\n   disabled on each SelectIO pin.\nPUDC_B must be tied either directly, or via a ≤ 1 kΩ to\nVCCO_14 or GND.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -36.068 50.038 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "12dee26f-11b3-4f2d-a5e8-a0ef058d319e")
	)
	(text "• For master modes: The FPGA can optionally switch to\n  EMCCLK as the clock source, instead of the internal\n  oscillator, for driving the internal configuration engine. The\n  EMCCLK frequency can optionally be divided via a\n  bitstream setting (ExtMasterCclk_en) and is forwarded for\n  output as the master CCLK signal.\n• For JTAG and slave modes: EMCCLK is ignored in the\n  JTAG and slave modes and can be left unconnected.\n\n=> we leave EMCCLK unconnected and don't use it in either JTAG  (never used) or SPI 4x mode (optional)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -70.612 76.2 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "27682e32-9e7d-4057-aa36-aa688a55c9e3")
	)
	(text "oups, backward (14 <=> 15)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 213.106 58.928 90)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "36dfcb9b-1c89-4506-a365-3f2ebb6454ec")
	)
	(text "/!\\ SPI signals cannot move\nThey have to be connected to DO[3..0] & FCS\nin x4 mode."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 61.976 39.37 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify right)
		)
		(uuid "4a0fd414-f10c-49ad-83fb-8f2c316a52d9")
	)
	(text "Bank 15"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 272.034 100.584 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "6cede5cb-ddba-425a-8d86-b34ae6b373ed")
	)
	(text "Two single-ended clocks going to MRCC/P pins.\n100 Mhz is common value for FPGA and useful for system clocking.\n54 MHz can easily be turned into video clocks for e.g. HDMI.\n\nThose are sample frequencies. Any oscillator in SMD3225-4P supporting\n3V3 operation can be used instead to get different frequencies with\nonly a BoM change\n\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 215.392 138.938 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "88a0bf27-dc20-4ed0-83bd-8dc94748fd65")
	)
	(text "Bank 14"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 272.034 57.404 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "a4877bfa-3fe7-4c37-82fa-5d1bbea3cc41")
	)
	(text "Bank 14 and 15 are 3.3V by default and for user.\nOnly exception is one MRCC/p signal is used i neach bank for clocks."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 144.018 18.034 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "bdef8125-8a44-4b38-8f80-5dbca71dddad")
	)
